SIMPLE: nock
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nock
<hw>Nock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Notch</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A notch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He took his arrow by the <qex>nock</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The upper fore corner of a boom
sail or of a trysail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nock</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nock
<hw>Nock</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To notch; to fit to the string, as
an arrow; to string, as a bow.</def> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noctambulation</ent>⟦br⟧
